  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 395°F/ Gas 6</p>\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Remove the leaves from the <strong>cauliflower<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>and trim the root </p>\n<p>Heat a large pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> over a medium-high heat </p>\n<p>Once boiling, add the <strong>whole cauliflower<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>and cook for 7 min</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Lato;font-size:15px;white-space:pre-wrap;\"> </span></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1836.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1836.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1836.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1836.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1836.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and chop the <strong>potatoes</strong> into bite-sized pieces </p>\n<p>Once ready, remove the <strong>cauliflower<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> from the pot and transfer to a baking tray (reserve the pot and water!) </p>\n<p>Leave the <strong>cauliflower</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]</strong> </span>to steam-dry for 5 min</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1836.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1836.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1836.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1836.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1836.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to the<strong> reserved cauliflower water</strong> and bring to a boil over a medium-high heat </p>\n<p>Cook for 15-20 min or until the potatoes are very soft </p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1836.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1836.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1836.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1836.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1836.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>pecans</strong> to the other side of the baking tray and drizzle with the <strong>agave nectar </strong></p>\n<p>Drizzle the <strong>cauliflower</strong> with a generous glug of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> </p>\n<p>Put the baking tray in the oven and cook for 20 min, removing the <strong>pecans</strong> after 7 min</p>\n<p>Once removed, leave the <strong>agave nectar</strong> to set on the <strong>pecans </strong>– these are your<strong> candied pecans</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1836.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1836.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1836.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1836.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1836.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and crush or grate the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\n<p>Chop the<strong> parsley </strong>very finely </p>\n<p>Chop the <strong>capers</strong> roughly </p>\n<p>Combine the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>capers</strong>, <strong>parsley</strong>, <strong>red wine vinegar</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong> and 50ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> with a splash of <strong>cold water</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>salsa verde</strong></p>\n<p>Tip: alternatively, you can use a blender to blitz everything!</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
